node.text:
I am positive some of you are hurting today. 

I am also positive some of you got more no’s or setbacks than you wanted to hear in the last week. 

I would just ask that you please hold on to the vision of the person that you’re becoming. 

He or she is worth it. I promise.

if you needed this drop a 🙏 below 

And share and save with someone who needs this. 
#bosslee

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JESSIE LEE | BOSSLEE MLM PRO on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Why network marketing?

Because no one can take it from me. 

You might know my story. And if you don’t, I was terminated wrongfully from my first company in 2017. Oh my God. Actually, tomorrow is my termination anniversary. LOL anyway, you cannot take my knowledge, skill set, determination, drive, or any other things needed to build a business from the ground up from me. So, I built it again. Only 6x bigger so far. 

This will never get old 🤣❤️

I’m using this photo to post this because I’ve never gotten political on my social media for the most part. But as I sit here watching people get their jobs taken from them because of a decision to make for their own body, I got to tell you…

THANK. GOD. For network marketing. Thank God for actual security in what I’m doing. 

Thank God for being paid for my skill set appropriately. Thank God I don’t have to show anybody any form of anything regarding my body in order to work. And, if for some reason this becomes totally mental and in order to exist in public you have to present a card, I get to work my business from my telephone. With my dogs. In my house. With my friends.

You can read into this however you want to I’m not having a discussion about it. But I will tell you right now I am forever thankful for my profession and never more than I am today given this climate. 

❤️
#bosslee

node.text:
“I am a GD Cheetah.”

I’m nearly positive I first discovered @glennondoyle Through a podcast. Maybe it was Brene Brown…Lord only knows.

For some reason I was instantly compelled to buy her book Untamed. Honestly, it might have been the cover art. I believe the opening quote of this caption ended her introduction to the book. 

It is rare that I devour a book cover to cover without putting it down. 

She was so raw. So vulnerable. Was saying all the things that so often I felt like I wanted to say but it just isn’t what girls should.

So I read. And I recommended it loudly. And I started shifting. 

I’m not crazy. I’m brave. I still stumble and of course want affection and to be soft while being brave and that SUCKS and is one hell of a journey. It’s not easy to be human. It’s not easy to be a powerful woman. It’s not lonely because of business and friendships. It’s lonely because I intimidate weak men. 

But like she said, and I loved “the braver I am, the luckier I get.” 

So I keep shooting. In business. In friendships. In life. In love. 

If you haven’t consumed Glennon’s content, you should. If for nothing else so you can see what authenticity looks like when it’s oozing out of someone’s soul so beautifully. 

I’m Jessie Lee, and I AM a GD cheetah. Are you? 
#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing?

because it brought me to Texas and Texas is home.

i’ll never forget the first time I got off the plane in Dallas. It was 2012 and the very first thing I saw when I stepped out of the taxi in downtown Dallas was a jacked up truck. I watched as a cowboy climbed out. He had a huge belt buckle, super tight jeans, and a black cowboy hat. i’m from a country town in Maryland but even I got to tell you I didn’t think Cowboys like that existed outside of country music television. 🤣

ironically, I was raised to hate Texas. My mother is about as far left as you can go and I was told the state was full of poisonous people. 😆🤣

it was the first time I ever extended a trip. I didn’t want to leave. I started posting on my social media how someday I would live in Texas.

someday happened three years ago. And now, Texas is where most of our business is derived. A large majority of our six figure annual earners are conglomerated here in North Dallas. As they say, there is power in proximity.

Texas felt like home from the second I touched down. And to know that someday I will raise babies in a part of the country that shares the values I do, that still believes in God, and that is wildly accepting of everyone whole maintaining morals that I abide by is very exciting to me.

The freedom provided by this profession to live the life you want should not be ignored.

Where do you think you’ll plant your roots and call home someday?

#bosslee

node.text:
Some of you are newer followers and need to know how much the book daring greatly by Brene Brown impacted my life on such a profound level.

I read the book right before I decided to board a plane and basically change everything in my life at the beginning of June 2020.

because of reading her book I was able to release all kinds of feelings I had around shame and what I was supposed to be as a woman, a business owner, single, etc.

I spent an entire 40 days of 2020 in Italy and Spain and as the days went on my energy got lighter, I said yeah, sure to literally hundreds of things I’ve always said no to, and for the first time in my life I really felt like I was living.

Since reading the book over the last year I have spent hours devouring her material. It has transformed my life. I cannot recommend her enough.

Shame. What a b.

Live your life. If you would like to go to Italia someday, drop a ❤️ below. 

#bosslee

P.s. damn you IG for cutting off such a cute photo lol

node.text:
The first personality type book I ever read sorted the personalities into birds.

I took the test. It told me I was an eagle. As if I didn’t know that.

regardless of what the book said I remember learning about bald eagles in elementary school. I remember learning about how rare they are, how dominant they are, how they operate on their own and how they can be commanding.

they represent the entire United States of America. I knew I resonated with that.

The other birds were owl, peacock, and dove. 

Which one do you think you are?

Characteristics: Domineering, strong-willed, independent, vocal, competitive and shrewd. How to motivate an eagle: Recognise their successes, offer them variation and give them the status they crave. Be firm and direct in your handling.

Read: also #bosslee
